text: today I'm making my very own sweet spot
underneath the Eiffel Tower in Paris who
says you've got to go to a fancy
restaurant to get an amazing French
experience
so for my picnics today I just stopped
at little local eateries along the way
and I got some french fries some fresh
baguettes some handmade french
chocolates and a couple of cream puffs
for dessert it is the location and the
French weather today that's making this
a truly unforgettable experience
a couple of insider tips for your eiffel
tower picnic if you're going to bring
some French wine don't forget to bring a
corkscrew and there's tons of room to
sit don't need to bring something to sit
on because the ground can sometimes be a
little bit wet
